//Question : Sum of dependencies in a graph
//Given a directed graph with V nodes and E edges, if there is an edge from u to v, then we will say that u depends on v. Number of Dependencies (NoD) for a node x is the total count of nodes that x depends upon. 
//Find out the sum of number of dependencies of every node.

class Solution {
    int sumOfDependencies(ArrayList<ArrayList<Integer>> adj, int V) {
        // code here
        int sum=0;
        for(int i=0;i<V;i++)
          sum+=adj.get(i).size();
        return sum;  
    }
};
